 How to Use External Databases in Neurodiagnoses
To enhance the accuracy of our diagnostic models, Neurodiagnoses integrates data from multiple biomedical and neurological research databases. If you are a researcher, follow these steps to access, prepare, and integrate data into the Neurodiagnoses framework.

1️⃣ Register for Access
Each database requires a separate registration and access approval. Follow the official access guidelines for each platform.

2️⃣ Download & Prepare Data
Once granted access, download datasets following the specific data usage terms. Ensure the files meet Neurodiagnoses' format requirements for integration.

Supported File Formats: .csv, .tsv, .nii (neuroimaging), .fasta (genetics)
Mandatory Fields for Integration: Subject ID, Diagnosis, Biomarkers, Genetic Data, Neuroimaging Metadata
3️⃣ Upload Data to Neurodiagnoses
Option 1: Manually upload to EBRAINS Bucket → [Collabs/neurodiagnoses/Bucket]
Option 2: Contribute via GitHub Repository → [GitHub: /data]
📌 Note: For large datasets, contact the project administrators before uploading.

4️⃣ Integrate with AI Models
Use Jupyter Notebooks on EBRAINS to preprocess and analyze data.
Run data harmonization scripts to standardize formats.
Train AI models with newly integrated patient cohorts.
2️⃣ Database Sources Table (GitHub & EBRAINS Wiki)
Where to Insert This:
📂 GitHub: docs/data_sources.md
📂 EBRAINS: Collabs/neurodiagnoses/Data Sources

🧠 Key Databases for Neurodiagnoses
Database	Focus Area	Data Type	Access Link
ADNI	Alzheimer's Disease	MRI, PET, CSF, cognitive tests	ADNI
PPMI	Parkinson’s Disease	Imaging, biospecimens	PPMI
GP2	Genetic Data for PD	Whole-genome sequencing	GP2
Enroll-HD	Huntington’s Disease	Clinical, genetic, imaging	Enroll-HD
GAAIN	Alzheimer's & Cognitive Decline	Multi-source database	GAAIN
UK Biobank	Population-wide studies	Genetic, imaging, health records	UK Biobank
DPUK	Dementia & Aging	Imaging, genetics, lifestyle	DPUK
PRION Registry	Prion Diseases	Clinical and genetic data	PRION
DECIPHER	Rare Genetic Disorders	Genomic variants	DECIPHER
📌 More Data Sources? If you know a relevant dataset, submit a proposal in [GitHub: /issues].

